DIGEST
SB 185 Original 2026 Regular Session Pressly
Proposed law provides that any agreement involving a victim of child sexual abuse that
prevents, or has the effect of preventing, the victim from disclosing or discussing the abuse
involving the victim is judicially enforceable, is null and void, and against public policy.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Adds R.S. 9:2717.5)
